. Her teaching stressed the importance of data in the management of MCH programs. Her research interest focused on differences in pregnancy outcomes and young children growth between ethnic groups in Hawaii.</p>	<p>Earlier in her career, in recognition of her international work in India and Bangladesh and in academe Dr. Baruffi has been awarded the title of Cavaliere d’Italia and the honorary citizenship of the city of Caravaggio (her residence in Italy).	  	  After she retired in 2007, she continued to participate in the Title V program applications review of the Pacific Islands; and still is an active member of the MCHJ editorial group.</p>    <h2><a id="mchn"></a>Interview</h2>			<p>Click below to listen to Gladiola Baruffi's story as  an MCH leader in academe.</p>            <button class="accordion">Career to becoming a leader in an MCH training program</button>        <div class="panel">          <div class="vidwrap">          <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/468700900" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>          </div>        </div>              <button class="accordion">Special skills or knowledge in leading an MCH training grant</button>        <div class="panel">          <div class="vidwrap">          <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/468701809" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>          </div>        </div>        <button class="accordion">Uniqueness in leading an MCH training grant</button>        <div class="panel">          <div class="vidwrap">          <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/468734554" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>          </div>        </div>     <button class="accordion">Benefits on becoming a leader in an MCH training grant</button>        <div class="panel">          <div class="vidwrap"